  "verdict": "FEASIBLE root-kill. A 2-input AND-gated self-destruct on 5%-leak recognizers gives normal-cell false-death ~4e-11 (therapeutic index ~2e+10) -- killing the cell via its OWN apoptosis only when 2 independent mutation/metabolite signals co-occur. The kill/specificity TRADE-OFF: single-cell tumour-kill drops to ~0.99 at N=2 (a cell escapes if not all N fire) -- but the resistance-agnostic BYSTANDER DEATH WAVE (RUNG-13/21, cures across 4-13% escapees) clears those, so partial single-cell kill is sufficient at the tumour level. Death module precedent: iCasp9 (clinical CAR-T safety switch) = engineered apoptosis-on-demand is proven.",
  "residuals": "Assumes recognizer leaks are INDEPENDENT -- correlated failure (a stressed normal cell mis-firing several recognizers; shared delivery/cell-state) degrades the AND multiplication and is the key risk to test. Also: the death module itself must be non-leaky (basal iCasp9 must not trigger); delivery of the multi-component circuit; kinetics (does effector cross threshold before the cell adapts?) -- a full eARM ODE of the coupled circuit + in-cell validation are the next/wet steps. This quantifies the SPECIFICITY logic of the kill-coupling, not a built circuit."
